<subSubSection id="C34472A7FFE7683A459A34F4BA90FDEC" pageId="18" pageNumber="301" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFE7683A459A34F4BA90FDEC" blockId="18.[151,1437,150,609]" pageId="18" pageNumber="301">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFE7683A459A34F4BB40FD94" bold="true" box="[199,315,511,537]" pageId="18" pageNumber="301">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFE7683A441E34F4B846FD95" baseAuthorityName="Neboiss" baseAuthorityYear="1994" box="[323,573,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Nyctiophylax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicatus">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFE7683A441E34F4B846FD95" box="[323,573,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="301">Nyctiophylax apicatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has previously been recorded from many localities on Cape York Peninsula, North 
<collectingRegion id="499AEFCEFFE7683A45BD3728BB1CFDB0" box="[224,359,547,573]" country="Australia" name="Queensland" pageId="18" pageNumber="301">Queensland</collectingRegion>
, and two localities in the NT (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF5CDDFFE7683A47E13728B920FDB0" author="Neboiss, A." box="[700,859,547,573]" pageId="18" pageNumber="301" pagination="191 - 205" refId="ref15513" refString="Neboiss, A. (1994) A review of the genus Paranyctiophylax Tsuda from Sulawesi, Papua New Guinea and northern Australia (Trichoptera: Polycentropodidae). Memoirs of the Museum of Victoria, 54, 191 - 205. https: // doi. org / 10.24199 / j. mmv. 1994.54.09" type="journal article" year="1994">Neboiss 1994</bibRefCitation>
). The species is recorded from a further ten sites in the NT.
</paragraph>
